msgid "Vascular catheter association"
msgstr ""

#, priority:10
msgctxt "dataElements/NEOIPC_BSI_DEV_ASS/DESCRIPTION"
msgid "An infection is considered as vascular catheter-associated if the catheter has been present for at least three consecutive days on the day of infection (=first symptoms or first positive diagnostic test; e.g. culture) or the day before. Both, central venous catheter (CVC) association and peripheral venous catheter (PVC) association are recorded. If a patient developing a bloodstream infection meets the criteria for both, PVC- and CVC-association, the CVC is considered as the device with the relatively higher infection risk and the BSI should be recorded as CVC-associated BSI."
msgstr ""

